record_data.record_plain_text: Sandy Ridge Wind, LLC FERC Electric Tariff 1. Availability. Sandy Ridge Wind, LLC (Seller) makes electric energy, capacity and ancillary services available under this Tariff to any purchaser for resale within the balancing authority area of PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. (PJM). 2. Applicability. This Tariff is applicable to all sales of energy, capacity and ancillary services by Seller which are subject to the jurisdiction of this Commission. 3. Rates. All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller. 4. Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between Seller and the purchaser. 5. Ancillary Services. Seller will make available to any purchaser the following ancillary services: a. PJM: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection. 6. Compliance with Commission Regulations. Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning sellers market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the sellers market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning sellers market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff. 7. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority. The Commission granted Seller in Docket No. ER11-113-000 the following waivers and blanket authorization: (a) waiver of Subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commissions regulations requiring the filing of cost-of-service information, except for sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16; and (b) Part 41, Part 101; (b) waiver of Part 141 of the Commissions regulations concerning accounting and reporting requirements, with the exception of 18 C.F.R. §§ 141.14 and 141.15; (c) blanket approval as to Section 204 of the FPA and Part 34 of the Commissions regulations for all future issuances of securities and debt and assumption of liabilities. 8. Modifications. Seller may unilaterally apply, under Federal Power Act section 205 and the regulations promulgated thereunder, to the Commission or other regulatory agency having jurisdiction for a modification of this Rate Schedule. 9. Seller Category. Seller is a Category 1 Seller in the Southeast, Central, Southwest Power Pool (SPP), Southwest, and Northwest regions, and a Category 2 Seller in the Northeast region, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a). 10. Effective Date. This tariff is effective upon the date authorized by the Commission.

SANDY RIDGE WIND, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Sandy Ridge Wind, LLC ("Sandy Ridge") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Sandy Ridge generating facility ("Sandy Ridge Facility").
The Sandy Ridge Facility is a wind generating facility located in Centre County, Pennsylvania. The Sandy Ridge Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Mid-Atlantic Interstate Transmission, LLC and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Sandy Ridge's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Sandy Ridge Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Sandy Ridge's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Sandy Ridge shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $180,000.00 The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $15,000.00

505867694.7 1 CO-TENANCY AND SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT THIS CO-TENANCY AND SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT (this “Agreement”) is made as of November 7, 2022 (“Agreement Date”) by and among SANDY RIDGE WIND, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company, in its individual capacity (“Sandy Ridge 1”) and as the initial Manager hereunder, SANDY RIDGE WIND 2, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Sandy Ridge 2”), and SANDY RIDGE TRANSCO INTERCONNECTION, LLC (“Transco”). Sandy Ridge 1 and Sandy Ridge 2 are collectively referred to herein as the “Project Companies” and individually as a “Project Company”. The Manager (as defined herein) and Transco are collectively referred to herein as the “Manager Parties” and individually as a “Manager Party”. The Project Companies, together with the Manager Parties, are collectively referred to herein as the “Parties” or individually as a “Party”. The terms “Party” and “Project Company” shall include the permitted successors and permitted assignees of such Person. Certain capitalized terms used in this Agreement are given defined meanings in Appendix A attached hereto. RECITALS A. Sandy Ridge 1 owns and operates an approximately 50 MW (or, upon repowering, up to 62.7 MW) wind energy electricity generation project and certain related interconnection facilities located in Blair and Centre County, Pennsylvania (“Sandy Ridge 1 Project”). B. Sandy Ridge 2 is constructing an 87.6 MW (approximate) wind energy electricity generation project and certain related interconnection facilities located in Blair and Centre County, Pennsylvania (“Sandy Ridge 2 Project”). The Sandy Ridge 1 Project and the Sandy Ridge 2 Project are each individually referred to herein as a “Project,” and collectively as the “Projects.” C. The Project Companies are the sole members of Transco. On or prior to the date hereof, (i) Sandy Ridge 1, Transco, PJM Interconnection, L.L.C., the regional transmission organization for the PJM region (“PJM”) and Mid-Atlantic Interstate Transmission, LLC (“MAIT”) entered into a Consent to Assignment Agreement and Agreement to Amend in respect of that certain Interconnection Service Agreement by and among Sandy Ridge 1, PJM and MAIT, with an effective date of May 12, 2021 (as may be further amended from time-to-time, together with all agreements, schedules, appendices, exhibits and other documents ancillary thereto, the “Interconnection Agreement”) and related ancillary agreements, by which PJM and MAIT consented to the assignment by Sandy Ridge 1 to Transco, and the assumption by Transco, of all rights, duties, and obligations of Sandy Ridge 1 under the Interconnection Agreement and related ancillary agreements (the “Interconnection Assignment Consent”), and (ii) in accordance with the terms thereof, Sandy Ridge 1 has assigned to Transco, and Transco has assumed, all rights, duties, and obligations of Sandy Ridge 1 under the Interconnection Agreement and such ancillary agreements, in accordance with the terms and conditions of the Interconnection Assignment Consent (the “Interconnection Assignment”), and Transco has become a party to the Interconnection Agreement and has the rights, entitlements, obligations, responsibilities and
505867694.7 2 liabilities in, to and under the Interconnection Agreement necessary for the Project Companies to interconnect their respective Projects. D. On or prior to the date hereof, Sandy Ridge 1 and Sandy Ridge 2 have executed and delivered that certain Substation and Facilities Easement Agreement dated as of the date hereof (“Substation Easement”), wherein Sandy Ridge 1 grants Sandy Ridge 2 certain easement rights over certain real property described in the Substation Easement (“Substation Easement Property”), which allows Sandy Ridge 2 to use, construct, operate, and maintain certain facilities, including a substation, for the Sandy Ridge 2 Project. E. The Project Companies each hold leasehold, easement, and license rights described in Exhibit A (together with the Substation Easement, the “Land Rights Agreements”) relating to the parcels of real property described in Exhibit B and the portions of real property where certain Shared Facilities will be located generally depicted in Exhibit B (together with the Substation Easement Property, “Joint Use Areas”). F. The Parties desire to provide in this Agreement for: (i) the co-ownership of certain Shared Facilities necessary or convenient to each Project Company’s ownership, development and operation of its respective Project; (ii) sharing of the use of such Shared Facilities for purposes of each Project Company’s development and operation of its respective Project; (iii) sharing use of the Joint Use Areas by each Project Company for its respective Project; (iv) sharing of certain costs related to such Joint Use Areas and the construction and use and operation of such Shared Facilities; and (v) the authorization of and grant of certain rights to Transco with respect to the Interconnection Agreement and related matters as set forth herein; all subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement. G. The Project Companies also wish to contract with the Manager for the provision of services to be performed with respect to the Shared Facilities and Joint Use Areas, and the Manager wishes to accept said engagement, on the terms and conditions contained herein. NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual promises contained herein, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which are hereby acknowledged by the Parties, the Parties agree as follows: ARTICLE 1 DEFINITIONS AND INTERPRETATIONS 1.1 Definitions. As used in this Agreement, including the Recitals, and except as required by grammatical usage and apart from proper nouns, each capitalized term has the meaning given to it in this Agreement and in the Schedule of Definitions attached as Appendix A. 1.2 Interpretation. In this Agreement, unless a clear, contrary intention appears: (a) the singular includes the plural and vice versa; (b) reference to any Person includes such Person’s successors and assigns but only if such assigns are permitted by this Agreement, and reference to a Person in a particular capacity excludes such Person in any other capacity; (c) reference to any gender includes each other gender; (d) reference to any agreement (including this Agreement), document or instrument means such agreement, document or instrument as amended or modified
505867694.7 3 and in effect from time to time in accordance with the terms thereof and, if applicable, the terms of this Agreement; (e) reference to any Governmental Requirement means such Governmental Requirement as amended, modified, codified, or reenacted, in whole or in part, and in effect from time to time, including, if applicable, rules and regulations promulgated thereunder; (f) reference to any Section means such Section of this Agreement, and references in any Section or definition to any clause means such clause of such Section or definition; (g) “hereunder,” “hereof,” “hereto” and words of similar import shall be deemed references to this Agreement as a whole and not to any particular Section or other provision of this Agreement; (h) “including” means including without limiting the generality of any description such term; and (i) relative to the determination of any period of time, “from” means “from and including”, “to” means “to but excluding” and “through” means “through and including”. ARTICLE 2 INTERCONNECTION AGREEMENT; SHARED FACILITIES; JOINT USE AREAS 2.1 Interconnection Agreement. (a) The Project Companies hereby acknowledge, agree and confirm, each as an owner of a portion of the “Customer Facility” identified in, and as defined in, the Interconnection Agreement, Sandy Ridge 1 was authorized to enter into the Interconnection Agreement and all agreements ancillary thereto in respect of such Customer Facility, to file the Interconnection Agreement with FERC and, prior to assignment of the Interconnection Agreement to Transco, to represent control of all portions of the Customer Facility for all purposes thereunder and to otherwise exercise all rights and perform all obligations of the “Interconnection Customer” thereunder. (b) Upon and following the Interconnection Assignment, (i) Transco became a party to the Interconnection Agreement and has all rights, entitlements, obligations, responsibilities and liabilities in, to and under the Interconnection Agreement necessary for the Project Companies to interconnect their respective Projects; (ii) Transco is and shall at all times be authorized to represent control of the “Customer Facility” identified in the Interconnection Agreement for all purposes thereunder and to exercise all rights and perform all obligations of the “Interconnection Customer” thereunder; (iii) Transco has the right to use and operate the Shared Facilities (including the right to direct the Manager with respect thereto, including curtailment thereof) as needed to comply with the terms of the Interconnection Agreement and to transmit the power from each Project to the Interconnection Facilities on behalf of the Project Companies, as members of Transco. (c) The Manager shall file this Agreement for acceptance by FERC pursuant to Section 4.11, and Sandy Ridge 2 shall execute and file a notice of concurrence with FERC concurrent therewith. By executing this Agreement, Transco hereby accepts the rights granted to Transco by the foregoing and authorizes the Manager, on behalf of Transco and the Project Companies, to make the foregoing FERC filing and coordinate the filings of the notices of concurrence as provided above; provided that neither Transco nor the Manager shall make such FERC filing unless each of the Project Companies has reviewed and approved the form and content thereof.
505867694.7 4 2.2 Shared Facilities. (a) The Project Companies hereby declare that their relationship in and to the Shared Facilities is and will be that of tenants in common, and that each Project Company will have an undivided interest in the Shared Facilities in proportion to its Proportionate Share as set forth on Exhibit D on and subject to the terms, conditions, limitations and requirements set forth in this Agreement. The arrangements and ownership structure contemplated by this Agreement are not being made with the intention or expectation of producing revenue or making or sharing in any profits from the ownership or operation of the Shared Facilities, but are instead intended as a form of legal ownership whereby the Project Companies can accomplish their respective objectives of independently owning and operating their respective Undivided Interests (as defined in Section 2.2(c)) in, and sharing the use of, the Shared Facilities in connection with their respective Projects and businesses and to enable the Project Companies to perform and discharge certain of their obligations under the Interconnection Agreement, and their respective Power Purchase Agreements. (b) Sandy Ridge 1 has constructed and is currently operating a substation on the Joint Use Areas which includes portions of the facilities for electrical transmission, interconnection, communications and other structures and facilities for shared use of the Parties as identified on Exhibit C-1 (the “Existing Shared Facilities”). The Project Companies intend to construct certain additions and upgrades to the Existing Shared Facilities identified on Exhibit C-2 for shared use by the Project Companies (“Shared Facilities Enhancements”, and together with the Existing Shared Facilities as further altered or reconstructed in accordance with this Agreement, the “Shared Facilities”). The initial plans in place as of the Agreement Date for the Shared Facilities Enhancements are identified on Exhibit C-2 attached hereto (herein, the “Shared Facilities Enhancement Plans”). Sandy Ridge 2 shall act as the Constructing Party for purposes of the design, procurement, installation and construction of the Shared Facilities Enhancements as identified in the Shared Facilities Enhancement Plans, all as more particularly set forth in Section 2.6 below. (c) Upon the Sandy Ridge 2 Acquisition Date, Sandy Ridge 1 shall be deemed to have GRANTED, SOLD, TRANSFERRED, ASSIGNED, and CONVEYED, and does hereby GRANT, SELL, TRANSFER, ASSIGN, AND CONVEY unto Sandy Ridge 2 an undivided ownership interest in and to the Existing Shared Facilities, including rights under construction and supply contracts and contractor, supplier or manufacturer warranties related to such Existing Shared Facilities, in each case in proportion to the Proportionate Share of the respective Project Companies, AS IS, WITH ALL FAULTS AND WITHOUT ANY REPRESENTATIONS OR WARRANTIES WHATSOEVER, EITHER EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, AND SPECIFICALLY EXCLUDING ANY WARRANTY OF TITLE, MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, OR ANY OTHER WARRANTY ARISING UNDER STATUTORY OR COMMON LAW. As each further component of the Shared Facilities (whether the Shared Facilities Enhancements or any Additional Facilities) is constructed and installed, without limiting the reimbursement terms set forth in this Agreement, the Constructing Party shall be deemed to have GRANTED, SOLD, TRANSFERRED, ASSIGNED, and CONVEYED, and does hereby GRANT, SELL, TRANSFER, ASSIGN, AND CONVEY unto each of the Project Companies an undivided ownership interest in and to such further component of Shared Facilities (whether the Shared Facilities Enhancements or any Additional Facilities),
505867694.7 5 including rights under construction and supply contracts and contractor, supplier or manufacturer warranties related to such Shared Facilities, in each case in proportion to the Proportionate Share of the respective transferee Project Companies, AS IS, WITH ALL FAULTS AND WITHOUT ANY REPRESENTATIONS OR WARRANTIES WHATSOEVER, EITHER EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, AND SPECIFICALLY EXCLUDING ANY WARRANTY OF TITLE, MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, OR ANY OTHER WARRANTY ARISING UNDER STATUTORY OR COMMON LAW. The intent of the foregoing is that each Project Company shall acquire and hold an undivided tenancy in common interest in each of the Shared Facilities (whether the Initial Shared Facilities or any Additional Facilities) in proportion to its respective Proportionate Share as set forth on Exhibit D for the benefit, operation and use of its respective Project as provided herein so as to provide for the joint ownership of the Shared Facilities (along with all appurtenant rights) by the Project Companies subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement. The foregoing undivided tenancy in common interest of each Project Company in the Shared Facilities may be referred to from time to time in this Agreement as an “Undivided Interest.” The GRANT, SALE, TRANSFER, ASSIGNMENT, and CONVEYANCE by and from Sandy Ridge 1 and/or the Constructing Party unto each of the Project Companies shall be self-operative and shall occur automatically without further action by any Project Company. Without limiting the foregoing, (i) upon the request of Sandy Ridge 2, Sandy Ridge 1 shall execute a bill-of-sale or other reasonably requested form of transfer acknowledging the GRANT, SALE, TRANSFER, ASSIGNMENT, and CONVEYANCE of the Existing Shared Facilities by and from Sandy Ridge 1 unto each of the Project Companies; and (ii) upon completion of the Shared Facilities Enhancements or any Additional Facilities, the Constructing Party shall, upon the request of any of the Project Companies, execute a bill-of-sale or other reasonably requested form of transfer acknowledging the GRANT, SALE, TRANSFER, ASSIGNMENT, and CONVEYANCE by and from the Constructing Party unto each of the Project Companies. Notwithstanding the foregoing or anything to the contrary herein, prior to the Sandy Ridge 2 Acquisition Date, Sandy Ridge 2 shall have a Proportionate Share equal to 0%. (d) For the avoidance of doubt, the Parties acknowledge and agree that the Shared Facilities include any Additional Facilities, but expressly do not include equipment, materials or other property (if any) identified in Exhibit C-1 and/or Exhibit C-2 as the sole property of any Project Company or other Person. (e) Each Project Company intends that all rights under construction and supply contracts and contractor, supplier or manufacturer warranties related to any Shared Facilities (whether the Initial Shared Facilities or any Additional Facilities) shall benefit all Project Companies, and the Project Companies shall cooperate with each other to ensure enforceability of such contracts and any warranties available under such contracts for the benefit of the Project Companies, including assigning such warranties to the Project Companies collectively if such warranties are assignable. (f) Each Project Company may use the Shared Facilities only to transmit electrical energy from the Projects to the Point of Interconnection. Neither Project Company will provide any interconnection or transmission services or rights to any other Person, except as required by FERC under the Federal Power Act.
505867694.7 6 2.3 Joint Use Areas. (a) A Project Company’s exercise of rights with respect to each portion of its Undivided Interest shall be subject to the Project Company having rights pursuant to Land Rights Agreements in favor of such Project Company to use the applicable Joint Use Areas on which the applicable Shared Facilities are located. Each Project Company shall comply with all the terms and conditions of the Land Rights Agreements to which it is a party. (b) The Land Rights Agreements as of the Agreement Date, including, if applicable, any such rights that are expected to be obtained after the Agreement Date, are described on Exhibit A in the Joint Use Areas generally depicted on Exhibit B. (c) The Land Rights Agreements to which each Project Company is a party are the separate property of such Project Company. Each Party hereby consents to the use of the Joint Use Areas by the other Parties pursuant to this Agreement, including without limitation, where such Joint Use Areas affect, or otherwise touch and concern, other real property interests or estates held by such Party so long as such use is consistent with the requirements of this Agreement and the rights of the Parties hereunder. For all purposes under this Agreement, the Project Companies shall share in use of the Joint Use Areas as contemplated by this Agreement and, in addition to sharing in the costs and expenses associated with the Shared Facilities as otherwise provided herein, shall share in the property taxes and rental payments and/or easement fees with respect to such Joint Use Areas in accordance with their Proportionate Shares. 2.4 Access to the Joint Use Areas and Shared Facilities. (a) By Project Companies. Subject to the conditions and additional rights described below, each Project Company and any Secured Party of any Project Company shall have access to and the right to enter onto the Joint Use Areas and the Shared Facilities located thereon to the extent reasonably necessary for (i) inspection of such Joint Use Areas and the Shared Facilities located thereon, without unduly interfering with the normal operations of the other Project Company or the Manager and otherwise subject to the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement, (ii) construction of the Shared Facilities in the event the Constructing Party fails to do so, in accordance with the terms hereof, (iii) Operation and Maintenance of the Shared Facilities in the event the Manager fails to do so, in accordance with the terms hereof, (iv) for ingress and egress to and from, and for maintenance or repair of, the Shared Facilities in the event of an Emergency and the failure or unavailability of the Manager or its representatives to respond timely to such Emergency, and (v) subject to the covenants, terms and conditions of this Agreement (including, without limitation, Sections 2.5 and 4.13), for ingress and egress to and from, and for construction, maintenance or repair of, any Separately Held Property of such Project Company that are located within or to be located within the Joint Use Areas pursuant to rights granted to such Project Company in the Land Rights Agreements to which it is a party. Except in the event of an Emergency, the accessing Project Company shall give the other Project Company and the Manager at least forty-eight (48) hours prior notice of its intent to enter upon the Joint Use Areas (said notice may be by telephone, e-mail, or any other recognized electronic means in addition to any other methods of notice authorized herein). In the event of an Emergency, prior notice is not required, but the accessing Project Company shall give notice of entry onto the Joint Use Areas to the other Project Company and the Manager as soon as reasonably practicable
505867694.7 7 thereafter). Any Project Company entering on the Joint Use Areas or accessing the Shared Facilities shall (1) follow all written safety and security procedures adopted by the Project Companies with respect to the Joint Use Areas and/or the Shared Facilities, and (2) not cause a breach or default of the terms of any binding Land Rights Agreements benefitting or burdening such Joint Use Areas where the terms thereof have been made available to the entering Project Company. (b) By Manager Parties. The Manager Parties shall have access to the Joint Use Areas and Shared Facilities at any time for purposes of complying with its obligations set forth in this Agreement, including (i) inspection of such Joint Use Areas and the Shared Facilities located thereon, without unduly interfering with the normal operations of the Project Companies and otherwise subject to the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement, (ii) Operation and Maintenance of the Shared Facilities, including repair thereof, in accordance with the terms hereof, or (iii) for ingress and egress to and from the Shared Facilities for the purposes set forth in the preceding items (i) and (ii). No notice to the Project Companies shall be required from a Manager Party prior to entering the Joint Use Areas in performing such Manager Party’s duties under this Agreement. While entering on the Joint Use Areas or accessing the Shared Facilities, the Manager Parties shall (1) follow all written safety and security procedures adopted by the Project Companies with respect to the Joint Use Areas and/or the Shared Facilities, and (2) not cause a breach or default of the terms of any binding Land Rights Agreements benefitting or burdening such Joint Use Areas where the terms thereof have been made available to such Manager Party. (c) By Secured Parties. A Secured Party of a Project Company shall have the right to enter onto the Joint Use Areas for the purposes described in Section 2.4(a)(i) and, in connection with or following the exercise of remedies by the Secured Party under its Security Documents, for the other purposes described in Section 2.4(a), in each case upon five (5) Business Days’ advance written notice of its entry delivered to the Manager and the Project Companies; provided that such right of entry shall be limited to normal business hours except in the case of an Emergency. Any Secured Party so entering on the Joint Use Areas or accessing the Shared Facilities shall (i) (1) follow all written safety and security procedures adopted by the Project Companies with respect to the Joint Use Areas and/or the Shared Facilities, and (2) not cause a breach or default of the terms of any binding Land Rights Agreements benefitting or burdening such Joint Use Areas where the terms thereof have been made available to the Project Company that is a debtor of such Secured Party, and (ii) not unduly interfere with the normal operations of the Project Companies and the Manager thereon. 2.5 No Interference. (d) Notwithstanding the other provisions of this Section 5.3: (1) The Manager Parties shall be authorized to curtail on a non-pro rata, but equitable and reasonable, basis (as determined by such Manager Party in good faith) if (A) in spite of such Manager Party’s good faith efforts to direct the Project Companies to comply with this Section 5.3, curtailment of deliveries from the Projects as directed by PJM or MAIT is not otherwise achievable, or (B) such non-pro rata allocation is otherwise necessary to comply with the Interconnection Agreement or PJM’s or MAIT’s direction, and, in each of the foregoing clauses (A) and (B), such non-pro rata allocation will not result in a default under the Interconnection Agreement; and (2) To the extent that the need for any curtailment, interruption or reduction can be attributed to a particular Project Company’s Project or portions of its Project or the failure of such Project to comply with the order to curtail or a default by such Project Company under this Agreement, the Interconnection Agreement, or an applicable Power Purchase Agreement, or to the extent such Project Company’s Project is the cause of an Emergency Condition or is directed by PJM or MAIT to curtail, then (A) all such

ARTICLE 6 MANAGER 6.1 Appointment of the Manager. The Manager shall cause the Shared Facilities to be operated and maintained and shall perform all of the Manager’s duties (x) in accordance with Good Utility Practice and all requirements of this Agreement; and (y) in a manner that does not violate or result in a breach of any Governmental Requirements, the Land Rights Agreements, the Interconnection Agreement
505867694.7 23 and any applicable requirements of FERC, NERC, PJM, and MAIT, and (z) in a manner that is (A) non-discriminatory, and (B) attempts to maximize the delivery of energy and energy-related products from the Projects to the Point of Interconnection at a reasonable cost. 6.2 Specific Authority. (d) To employ from time to time, at the expense of the Project Companies but subject to the Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget, persons, firms or corporations to perform Operation and Maintenance, including entering into an O&M Agreement; (e) To pay and collect amounts due under this Agreement in connection with the Land Rights Agreements and the Shared Facilities, and to maintain one or more bank accounts wherein funds received by the Manager in connection with its duties hereunder shall be maintained; (f) To expend monies necessary for Operation and Maintenance in accordance with the Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget (including any amounts in excess thereof permitted under this Agreement); (g) To commit to the expenditure of or spend such amounts for and on behalf of the Project Companies as are reasonably necessary to expedite Repairs to the Shared Facilities due to an Emergency up to and including Five Hundred Thousand Adjusted Dollars ($500,000) in the aggregate (including the costs of installation and expediting fees), provided that the Manager gives notice by electronic mail to the Project Companies regarding the nature and amount of the expenditure as soon as reasonably practicable after the estimated amount of the expenditure is
505867694.7 24 known by the Manager, but in any event no later than the time the Manager commits to the expenditure; (h) To negotiate with, and represent the Project Companies’ interests before any Governmental Authority regarding property valuation and real property taxes (if any) related to the Joint Use Areas and/or the Shared Facilities; and (i) to execute, acknowledge and deliver any and all instruments and take such other steps as are reasonably necessary to effectuate the foregoing and as are consistent with the terms of this Agreement, including Section 6.3 and any other limitations set forth herein. 6.3 Limitation on Authority. 505867694.7 25 (j) Except as provided in the Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget or as provided in Sections 3.5(c), 5.2(a) and 6.2(g), enter into any commitments, contracts or other agreements requiring expenditures in excess of One Hundred Fifty Thousand Adjusted Dollars ($150,000.00) or with a duration of more than two (2) years, except for (i) permitted expenditures in the case of an Emergency or as contemplated by the Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget, or (ii) expenditures under the O&M Agreement or any approved amendment thereto; (k) Except as permitted under Sections 7.9 and 7.10, procure insurance coverage that is less than the coverage required under Article 7; or (l) Enter into or materially modify any agreement with any Affiliate of the Manager in connection with performing Manager’s duties under this Agreement (including, without limitation, Repairs and/or Operation and Maintenance) or supplying services in connection with the performance of such duties, other than agreements approved as part of the financing of the Projects, except on terms and conditions, including price, that are at least as favorable to the Project Companies as would be obtained from an unaffiliated third-party. 6.4 Indemnification of the Manager Parties. ARTICLE 7 INSURANCE 7.1 Property Insurance. Unless the Parties otherwise agree and subject in any event to Sections 7.9 and 7.10 below, the Manager shall arrange for “all risk” property insurance during operations for the Shared Facilities; provided that each Party, at its discretion, may insure for its own business interruption losses. The “all risk” property insurance shall be on a replacement costs basis of the Shared Facilities. The policy may contain reasonable sub-limits for catastrophe or other similar perils. The Parties shall, and shall use commercially reasonable efforts to, cause their Secured Parties to, cooperate and endorse all loss proceeds checks or waive their requirement to be a loss payee and take all reasonable actions to ensure loss proceeds are processed promptly and in accordance with the intent of this Agreement. Any property insurance procured by the Manager shall be primary as to any other insurance of the Parties and such policy shall waive the right of subrogation against the Parties. The policy may contain reasonable sub-limits for catastrophe or other similar perils. The cost thereof shall be borne entirely by Sandy Ridge 2 with respect to the Shared Facilities Enhancements, but otherwise shall constitute Shared Facilities Construction Costs to be shared by the Project Companies in accordance with their respective Proportionate Shares. Such policies shall name each of the Parties and their Secured Parties as additional insureds and, to the extent obtainable on commercially reasonable terms, shall provide for thirty (30) days (ten (10) days in the case of non-payment of premiums) prior written notice before cancellation or modification. Once operational, all risk property insurance consistent with industry standards shall be procured in accordance with Section 7.1 above. 7.3 Liability Insurance. The Manager shall maintain liability insurance, including general liability coverage, covering the Joint Use Areas and the Shared Facilities, and each Project Company shall maintain liability insurance covering its Project and Property for any activities on the site of its Project or the Joint Use Areas. Each Party shall obtain and maintain commercial general liability insurance covering liability for bodily injury and death, property damage to third-parties and damage to property of third-parties in the care, custody and control of any Party and/or their respective employees in connection with operations at such Party’s Project and the Shared Facilities. Such coverage shall have a minimum limit of not less than Five Million Adjusted Dollars ($5,000,000.00) per occurrence and Ten Million Adjusted Dollars
505867694.7 29 ($10,000,000.00) annual aggregate for bodily injury and property damage, provided that such coverage (i) may be provided as part of a blanket policy covering other properties and may be provided by a combination of primary and excess policies, (ii) shall comply with any statutory obligation imposed by workers compensation or occupational disease laws, (iii) shall contain contractual liability and separation of insureds clause, and (iv) shall designate the Parties, the Secured Parties, and their officers, directors, employees and agents as additional insureds. If a policy described above is on a “claims made” basis, the retroactive date of the policy shall be the Agreement Date. The Parties shall each obtain and maintain minimum coverage to comply with any statutory obligation imposed by workers compensation or occupational disease (or employer’s liability) laws to the extent the Party uses its employees to perform duties under this Agreement. In the event the Party retains a subcontractor to perform any of such duties, it shall require such Person to comply with the requirements of this Section 7.4. 7.5 Automobile Liability. The Parties shall each also obtain and maintain an automobile liability insurance in the amounts they maintain for their other operations covering bodily injury and property damage, for hired, owned (if any) and non-owned vehicles to the extent their operations under this Agreement contemplate use of hired, owned and non-owned vehicles. 7.6 Casualty Event. In the event of a casualty that affects any of the Shared Facilities, all insurance proceeds with respect to the Shared Facilities shall be applied to reconstruction of the affected Shared Facilities. If there is uninsured loss or insurance proceeds are inadequate in connection with a casualty event occurring on or after the Sandy Ridge 2 Acquisition Date, the Project Companies shall contribute additional amounts based on their Proportionate Shares in the Shared Facilities; provided that additional amounts due with respect to any claims arising from the gross negligence or willful misconduct of a Party shall be first fully allocated to the account of such Party and then any balance not arising from the gross negligence or willful misconduct of such Party being contributed by the Project Companies based on their Proportionate Shares. All policies and binders with respect to insurance provided pursuant to this Article 7 shall be as follows: (a) Form of Policies. 505867694.7 31 (d) Certificates; Proof of Loss. ARTICLE 8 ASSIGNMENTS AND RIGHT TO ENCUMBER 8.1 Assignment by Parties. 505867694.7 33 any outstanding breaches or defaults of the assigning Party that are capable of being cured, (iv) the assignee agrees in writing, in form and substance reasonably satisfactory to the other Parties, to assume all of the present and future obligations of the assigning Party under this Agreement and to be bound by the terms of this Agreement in the place and stead of the assigning Party, to the extent of the interest assigned, and (v) a counterpart of the instrument of assignment, executed by the parties thereto, is delivered to the other Parties. 8.3 Right to Encumber. (c) Pledge, Collateral Assignment or Encumbrance. 505867694.7 34 Company hereunder, the non-defaulting Party declaring the default shall also provide written notice to the defaulting Party’s Secured Parties of such default (and accept their cure of such default on the terms set forth herein), (iii) each such Secured Party shall have the same period after receipt of a notice of default to cure, or cause to be cured, the default described therein, as is given to the defaulting Party, plus, in each instance, any additional cure periods provided under the Security Documents, not to exceed (a) thirty (30) days in the event of any monetary default; and (b) sixty (60) days in the event of any non-monetary default; provided, however, that such sixty (60)-day period shall be extended for the time reasonably required by the Secured Party to complete such cure (not to exceed one hundred twenty (120) days in the aggregate), so long as the Secured Party is diligently pursuing such cure, and (iv) in case of the bankruptcy, insolvency or appointment of a receiver in bankruptcy for a Project Company (the “Insolvent Party”), if this Agreement is terminated with respect to the Insolvent Party or rejected in such proceeding, the other Parties (the “Solvent Parties”) shall upon written request of the first priority Secured Party of the Insolvent Party, within thirty (30) days after the Secured Party obtains possession or control of the assets of the Insolvent Party, accept such Secured Party, or its designee or assignee, as a Party to this Agreement or enter into a new shared facilities agreement with respect to the Shared Facilities with such Secured Party, or its designee or assignee, within twenty (20) days after the receipt of such request. Such new Shared Facilities agreement shall be effective as of the date of the termination of this Agreement by reason of default by the Insolvent Party or upon the date of rejection of this Agreement by the Insolvent Party in its bankruptcy proceeding, on the same terms, covenants, conditions and agreements as contained in this Agreement. Upon acquisition of a Project Company’s Project by a Secured Party, whether through foreclosure of a Secured Party’s lien and security interests, by conveyance in lieu of foreclosure or otherwise, or upon the acceptance of the Secured Party, or its designee or assignee, as a Qualified Transferee and Party hereunder, or upon execution of any such new Shared Facilities agreement, the Secured Parties, or their designees or assignees, of the Insolvent Party shall perform or cause to be performed all of the covenants and agreements set forth in this Agreement to be performed by the Insolvent Party from and after such acquisition. All reasonable expenses, including reasonable attorneys’ fees, incurred by the Parties in connection with (i) the assignment or proposed assignment of a Party’s rights
505867694.7 35 under this Agreement, or (ii) the actual or proposed pledge, collateral assignment, encumbrance, or grant of a security interest in a Party’s rights under this Agreement to a Secured Party, shall be promptly paid by the assigning/borrowing Party to the respective Parties upon request therefor. 8.5 FERC Approval. In the event of an assignment or transfer in part by a Party pursuant to Section 8.1 above, the Parties shall, at the reasonable request and expense of the assigning Party, execute and deliver a separate agreement with such assignee together with any necessary amendment to this Agreement, such that this Agreement, as amended, and such separate agreement shall cumulatively allocate the respective rights of the assigning Party and the assignee following such assignment; provided that in no event shall such amendment or separate agreement increase any obligation or liability of any of the other Parties or otherwise adversely impact such Parties rights in and to the Joint Use Areas and Shared Facilities under this Agreement, without the express consent of such Party thereto. ARTICLE 9 TERM AND TERMINATION 9.1 Term and Termination. The term of this Agreement shall commence as of the Agreement Date and shall terminate, subject to obtaining any necessary prior FERC approvals for such termination, upon the mutual agreement of all of the Parties, with the consent of the then-existing Secured Parties, if applicable. Upon such termination, the Parties shall execute and record a notice of such termination with a reference to the Memorandum, as it may have been amended. 9.2 Termination as to a Project Company: Surrender of Interests. Any Project Company may elect to surrender all of its interests hereunder and in and to the Joint Use Areas and the Shared Facilities and to assign its rights hereunder to the other Project Companies, but only with the consent of the other Project Companies, and, thereupon, to cease to have any right, title or interest in this Agreement and Shared Facilities; provided that (A) the Surrendering Party executes and delivers all instruments of transfer as may be necessary or appropriate to effect (and that do effect) the assignment of such rights to the other Project Companies, in form and substance reasonably acceptable to the other Project Companies, (B) the Surrendering Party is not then in default of its obligations under this Agreement or the other Project Companies to which such rights are being assigned have agreed in writing to promptly cure such defaults, (C) each Secured Party that holds a security interest in such rights of the Surrendering Party being so surrendered has consented in writing to such surrender and assignment, which consent may be granted in its sole discretion, and has released or agreed to release such Secured Party’s security interest in the interests being assigned and in the Shared Facilities, and (D) the Surrendering Party has fulfilled and paid all then outstanding obligations under the applicable Security Documents. The Surrendering Party shall remain fully responsible for, and shall pay (i) its applicable Proportionate
505867694.7 36 Share of all Shared O&M Expenses and other obligations and liabilities hereunder through the effective date of its surrender and assignment, and (ii) its applicable Proportionate Share of the Shared Facilities Construction Costs (including in respect of any Additional Facilities that have been added prior to such surrender and assignment). In addition, the Surrendering Party shall be responsible for obtaining any FERC approval required for the transfer of the Surrendering Party’s interest in the Shared Facilities to the other Project Companies and the Surrendering Party shall be responsible for all costs associated with obtaining such rights. Notwithstanding the foregoing, if the Surrendering Party maintains, and will continue to maintain after such surrender, Separately Held Property of such Surrendering Party in any of the Joint Use Areas pursuant to rights granted to such Surrendering Party in the Land Rights Agreements to which such Surrendering Party is a party and will remain a party following such surrender, then (w) such Surrendering Party’s continued use of the Joint Use Areas shall comply with the terms of the Land Rights Agreements and shall not interfere with the use and enjoyment by any other Project Company of its respective rights in such Joint Use Areas, (x) such Surrendering Party shall cooperate with the Project Companies in good faith to accommodate use of the Joint Use Areas by each of the Project Companies; (y) such Surrendering Party shall not claim that the continued use of the Joint Use Areas and the Shared Facilities by the Project Companies pursuant to and in accordance with the terms of this Agreement, separately or in the aggregate, constitutes an overburdening of the Joint Use Areas or any portion thereof; and (z) such Surrendering Party shall execute a recordable acknowledgement of the provisions of this Section 9.2 and the Surrendering Party’s covenants set forth herein, in form and substance reasonably acceptable to the other Project Companies. 9.3 Abandonment or Decommissioning of a Project. In addition to the obligations set forth in Article 7 and Section 9.2, in the event a Surrendering Party desires to decommission and/or abandon its Project, the Surrendering Party shall, upon notice to the other Parties of its intent to decommission and/or abandon its Project, be responsible for the removal of any Shared Facilities no longer required by the remaining Parties due to the decommissioning and/or abandonment of the Surrendering Party’s Project, and upon the failure of the Surrendering Party to remove or release the subject Shared Facilities, any of the other Project Companies or the Manager may remove or release the subject Shared Facilities on behalf of such Surrendering Party and shall charge the Surrendering Party all costs incurred to accomplish such removal or release, plus ten percent (10%) of such costs for the services of the removing party in procuring and supervising such work. In addition, the Surrendering Party shall be responsible for and shall pay its Proportionate Share of all Shared O&M Expenses and other obligations and liabilities hereunder through the effective date of abandonment; the Surrendering Party shall further remain fully responsible for, and shall pay (i) its applicable Proportionate Share of all Shared O&M Expenses and other obligations and liabilities hereunder through the effective date of such abandonment, and (ii) its applicable Proportionate Share of the Shared Facilities Construction Costs (including in respect of any Additional Facilities that have been added prior to the effective date of such abandonment). 9.4 Distribution on Termination of this Agreement. In the event that the Project Companies decide to decommission all of the Projects and to proceed with the removal of the Shared Facilities, the Manager shall take account of the Shared Facilities, and any other assets or liabilities related thereto, and after obtaining any necessary FERC approvals, shall proceed with the liquidation thereof. The assets shall be liquidated under the supervision of the Manager as
505867694.7 37 promptly as is consistent with obtaining a reasonable value therefor, and the proceeds therefrom, together with any assets distributed in-kind, shall be applied and distributed as follows: 9.4.1 To the payment of debts and liabilities of the Parties to third-parties in connection with the Shared Facilities which are then due and the expenses of liquidation (including expenses incurred by the Manager) on a pro-rata and pari passu basis, based upon each Project Company’s Proportionate Share as of the date of liquidation. 9.4.2 To the setting up of any reserves which the Manager deems reasonably necessary for any contingent or unforeseen liabilities or obligations or debts not yet payable by the Parties in connection with Joint Use Areas and the Shared Facilities, including any reserves to pay costs associated with the decommissioning and removal of the Shared Facilities, provided that any Party may elect to Dispute, and to submit to arbitration, the amount determined by the Manager for any such reserves pursuant to Section 13.2 below. 9.4.3 Any sum remaining shall be distributed on a pro-rata basis to the Project Companies, based upon each Project Company’s Proportionate Share as of the date of final termination of this Agreement. 9.4.4 The Manager shall thereupon have the right, to disconnect the Shared Facilities from the Interconnection Facilities and the Projects, subject to obtaining any FERC approvals necessary for such actions. 9.5 Valuation and Distribution of Non-Cash Distributions. To the extent that non-cash consideration is distributed in kind as permitted herein, the fair market value of such assets shall first be determined by an independent valuation expert selected by the Parties, including separate valuations for each of the Shared Facilities, and the distribution of assets shall be made in accordance with such valuation. ARTICLE 10 DEFAULT AND REMEDIES 10.1 Project Company Default. 505867694.7 38 Agreement that is received by such Party to the other Parties, their Secured Parties and the Manager within forty-eight (48) hours of receiving such notice of default or breach, regardless of the party or the Land Rights Agreement that is alleged in the notice to be in default or to have been breached; (c) Breaches or causes the breach of the Interconnection Agreement and such defaulting Project Company fails to cure such breach by the time that is ten (10) days less than the specified cure period under the Interconnection Agreement, provided that in no event shall the resulting cure period available to the Project Company be less than five (5) Business Days. 505867694.7 39 following written notice from another Party to whom such amount is owed specifying the amount to be paid; (b) Makes an assignment for the benefit of creditors, files a petition in bankruptcy, voluntarily takes advantage of any bankruptcy or insolvency laws or is otherwise adjudicated bankrupt or judicially insolvent, in each case, immediately upon such occurrence or, if a petition or an answer is filed proposing the adjudication of the Manager as bankrupt, when the Manager shall consent to the filing thereof or sixty (60) days after the filing thereof unless the same shall have been discharged, opposed, or denied prior thereto; (c) Breaches, or causes the breach of the terms of a Land Rights Agreement and fails to cure such breach within the time permitted by the terms of such Land Rights Agreement, after receipt of a notice of default from a Party to cure, or cause to be cured, the default described therein, as is given to the Manager less, in each instance, the following reduced time periods: (i) five (5) days less than the specified cure period under the Land Rights Agreement in the event of any monetary default; and (ii) ten (10) days less than the specified cure period under the terms of the Land Rights Agreement in the event of any non-monetary default; (d) Fails to cure a default by the owner under the O&M Agreement within fifteen (15) days after its occurrence, in the case of such a default that can be cured by the payment of money, or forty-five (45) days after its occurrence, in the case of a default that cannot be cured solely by the payment of money; or (e) Fails to perform any other material covenant or obligation under this Agreement not covered by the foregoing clauses (a) through (d) within thirty (30) days following written notice from any Party specifying the nature of the failure to perform, provided that if the default is not reasonably capable of being cured within thirty (30) days, Manager shall have such additional period, not to exceed an additional sixty (60) days, to cure such failure. 505867694.7 40 (3) To disconnect the defaulting Project Company’s Project from the Shared Facilities, provided, that (A) the non-defaulting Project Company shall have in good faith determined that bringing an action for money damages and/or for specific performance will not provide an adequate or timely remedy for such default, and (B) all of the non-defaulting Project Companies shall have consented in writing to such disconnection; provided, further that the defaulting Project Company shall be permitted to reconnect promptly when and if the default is cured, any necessary approvals from Governmental Authorities, PJM and/or MAIT have been obtained, and in the case of any such reconnection, the non-defaulting Project Companies and the Manager shall have been compensated in full for any and all damage incurred by them as a result of such Project Company Event of Default; (4) To bring an action to specifically enforce the provisions of this Agreement; (5) To bring an action for money damages or other appropriate relief; or (6) To exercise any other rights and remedies which the non-defaulting Parties might have at law or in equity, other than termination of this Agreement.
